  Nigeria now has 45,687confirmed COVID-19 cases, with 443 new cases recorded on Friday night According to a tweet from the Nigeria Center for Disease Control, NCDC, 32,637 patients have now been discharged, with 936 patients losing their lives to the coronavirus. The tweet revealed that Plateau State had the highest number of infections on Friday night with 103 cases, with Lagos State following with 70 cases. Other states read as follows: FCT-60  Ondo-35  Edo-27  Rivers-27  Kaduna-20  Osun-19  Borno-18  Oyo-18  Kwara-11 Adamawa-9 Nasarawa-7 Gombe-6  Bayelsa-4  Imo-4  Bauchi-2  Ogun-2  Kano-1  443 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; Plateau-103Lagos-70FCT-60Ondo-35Edo-27Rivers-27Kaduna-20Osun-19Borno-18Oyo-18Kwara-11Adamawa-9Nasarawa-7Gombe-6Bayelsa-4Imo-4Bauchi-2Ogun-2Kano-1 45,687 confirmed32,637 discharged936 deaths pic.twitter.com/X2pZRogn59 — NCDC (@NCDCgov) August 7, 2020  